The incident took place on Thursday afternoon. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three taxi owners have been shot dead in Mabopane, north of Pretoria. The incident took place on Thursday afternoon. READ: Police launch manhunt following KZN mass killing Police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo says the motive for murders is unknown at the stage but ongoing taxi violence in the area cannot be ruled out. "Currently there are no witnesses but we are appealing to anyone who's got information that assist us in the investigation or to apprehend the suspect to please come forward," Masondo said.